<p>
                        
<lb n="1" />kō-vicaiya-nanti
<choice>
  <orig>c</orig>
  <reg>cc</reg>
</choice>ura-parumaṟk
                        
<lb n="2" break="no" />ku yāṇṭu muppattēḻā
                        
<lb n="3" break="no" />vatu
                </p>
                
                
<p>
                        vaḷḷipēṭu-nāṭuṭaiya vik
                        
<lb n="4" break="no" />kiramāttiya nāṭu mārikappā
                        
<lb n="5" break="no" />kiḻār makaṉ vakkaṭi paṭṭāṉ
                        
                </p>
                                
        </div>
        
        
         
<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                
<p n="1-3">
                        Tirthy-seventh year of the victorious king Nandīśvaravarman.
                </p>
                
                                
                
<p n="3-5">
                        Vakkaṭi, son 
<supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Mārikappākiḻar
<note>Mārikappāvakiḻār in 
<bibl n="Āvaṇam">
                        
<ptr target="bib:Avanam" /></bibl> introduction to the inscription.</note> 
<supplied reason="subaudible">in/of</supplied> the 
<foreign>nāṭu</foreign> of Vikramāditya, lord of Vaḷḷipēṭunātu, fell.
                </p>

         </div>
        
         
